deck: Descendent of Rasputin and member of the Moody coven.
description:
Origin

A distant descendent of Rasputin, Rasp joined the Moody coven as a young man.

Creation

Rasp was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. He made his first appearance in Klarion #1.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Rasp is attacked on the streets by some bullies, and is rescued by Klarion. He invites Klarion to live at the Moody Museum. He is targeted by Coal and Necrot as a likely consumer for their new technology, and is given the first buddybot by Coal. Jacked up by the power boost, he goes to the Necropolitan Club. When he sees Klarion and Zell together he lashes out jealously, and a fight ensues. Klarion brings him down, and together with Zell they escape the scene. Later, he spies on Klarion and Zell as they bond, but is distracted by the emergence of Contessa, his buddybot. The pair bond immediately, and spend time together until they are attacked by Klarion. Rasp protests, and is left alone with the now human-shaped Contessa. She encourages him to acquire more cybernetic enhancements to increase their closeness, and he agrees, sneaking out to the Necropolitan Club and acquiring several augmentations. Soon after h returns to the Moody Museum, and works with Klarion and the rest of the coven to defeat Gargora.

Powers and Abilities

Rasp possesses an inherent magical ability that has gone largely unexplained. He is obsessed with technology, and possesses several cybernetic implants. He is also very difficult to kill.

deck: A member of the Moody coven and friend of Klarion
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Zell's origin. At some point in her life she moved to New York and joined the Moody coven, though she had very little access to her inherent magic.

Creation

Zell was created by Ann Nocenti and Trevor McCarthy. She made her first appearance in Klarion #1.

Major Story Arcs

Klarion

Zell forms a fast friendship with Klarion, and the pair travel to the Necropolitan Club to help Rasp, who has gone to seek revenge on some bullies. She tries to convince Klarion to help Rasp, but he is unmoved. Once Klarion brings Rasp down, the three escape the scene. After being lectured by Piper, she demonstrates the ropes to Klarion. When they kiss, she accidentally strangles him with her hair, and he creates a magical explosion to escape. This explosion leads Klarion to discover the robot Contessa. Zell joins Klarion in investigating the robots, acquiring one of her own in the process. When they are attacked by Coal, and then by witch hunters, she gets left behind by Klarion and Beelzebub, though she follows them into Klarion's pocket soon after. There, she fights with Beelzebub, who accuses her of bewitching Klarion. She and Klarion argue about the virtues of the buddybots and his intention to ingest similar technology. When he does, she is expelled from the pocket along with the others. After Klarion leaves, she follows him to Beelzebub's barber shop, and chastises him for trying to abandon his new buddybot. She takes the new buddybot and returns to the Moody Museum, where she works with Klarion and the rest of the coven to defeat Gargora.

Powers and Abilities

Zell has largely unknown magical abilities. She has extremely long prehensile hair, which appears to move semi-independently of her will. She appears to possess a level of psychometric ability.

deck: Former member of Cheshire's Ravens. A professional killer with a lethal touch power. She plotted against her team to try to find a cure for the virus that gave her her meta-human power. It is unknown whether she survived the attempt at a cure, but Cheshire has sworn vengeance against her for her betrayal if she did.
description:
Story Line

Termina was one of Cheshire's original Ravens team, along with Pistolera, Vicious, and Cheshire herself. She and Cheshire were close, and Cheshire respected her and trusted her, even, perhaps, considered her a friend. She tricked and betrayed her and her teammates though, because she wanted to be rid of the disease that gave her her powers. She had learned that, in theory, a neutron radiation bath could kill the disease inside of her and let her be human again - the radiation might killer her along with the disease of course, but she was willing to take the risk.

Cheshire told her that she respected her choice, and even her betrayal, but that if she lived, she had made her an enemy and there would be a reckoning between them.

It was never revealed whether Termina survived the radiation or not, but she's made no other appearances since.
name: Termina

May Reilly was a woman born during the Industrial Revolution in a different reality and made herself a steampunk spider suit with 18th century looking machinary. She started calling herself Lady Spider and tried to be a hero in her own reality.

Creation

Lady Spider was created by Robbie Thompson and Denis Medri and first appeared in Spider-Verse Vol.1 issue 1 (2015).

Major Story Arcs

Spider-Verse

May lived her life, but was eventually recruited by Spider-UK and the Spider-Army to fight against Morlun and his family. May Reilly fought bravely and even gained a few new friendships. After Morlun was defeated, May joined a number of former Spider-Army members in becoming the guardians of the great Web, also known as the Web Warriors.

deck: Killer that sees through his guns, a victim of a school shooting.
description:
Major Story arcs

Grayson

The Old Gun was introduced in the series Grayson. It is explained that Christophe Tanner was victim of a school shooting in Geneva, the school that his two sons attended. The boys were both killed and Christophe lost the use of his eyes and had them removed. He then had surgery to connect his ocular nerves to his pistols, became part of the assassin community and took the name Old Gun.

Dick Grayson is tasked with capturing Old Gun after the gunman steals some enhanced eyes, ones that Spyral is looking for. Due to Grayson's hypnos being ineffective on Old Gun, he is accompanied by three other agents but the mission still fails. Later on, after asking Batman to research "Christophe Tanner", Grayson discovers Old Gun still has a son left and the boy has just started attending school. Dick is able to find Old Gun at the school and Tanner states that he took the eyes in a bid to connect himself to them but this process is not possible. Therefore, Tanner willingly hands over the eyes and even shares a joke with Grayson until he is shot by Alia, an agent of Spyral. Christophe retaliates and kills Alia before he dies of his wounds by his sons side.
name: The Old Gun
